data.value: Glaucoma is the most common cause of vision loss in people of working age. It is caused by pressure building up inside the eye which damages the optic nerve and usually affects both eyes. Research is currently looking into new ways to help deal with cataracts such as specially designed eye drops and methods that help release pressure inside the eye. Glaucoma effects 480,000 in the UK and 1 in 50 in Europe making it a common and serious issue (center, 2019). There are 4 different types of Glaucoma so it would be important to design my application to provide diagnosis of all them. Further treatments of Glaucoma can be achieved with laser surgery but early diagnosis is extremely important. My application will help educate people on the severity of each of these conditions and also potentially provide diagnosis that could be utilized by the medical sector
